  "prompt": "Which one is correct? 'If it was me' or 'if it were me'?",
  "response": "The correct phrase is \"if it were me.\"\n\nThis phrase uses the subjunctive mood, which is a verb form used to express hypothetical or non-real situations. \"If it were me\" is the grammatically correct usage when talking about situations that are contrary to fact or hypothetical.\n\nFor example:\n- \"If it were me, I would have handled the situation differently.\"\n\nUsing \"if it was me\" is commonly heard in informal speech, but \"if it were me\" is the proper usage in formal writing and speech.",
